724639f-a.text:
West Street, Vestry, to Lesbrosses. (Before Reconstruction)
President Borough of Manhatten.
CREIT LINE IIPEiATIVE.  June 9, 1919.
724639f-a.folder: West Street & Vestry Street, Manhattan, NY

724638f-a.text:
(1)
West Street, north from Vestry Street, showing foundation work for the southward extension of the West Side Express Highway. Buildings seen on the right are Nos. 268 and 270-271 West Street, adjoining
and at the S.E. corner of Desbrosses Street.
July 28, 1937.
P. L. Sperr.
(2)
The samme, showing only the east side of the street, north to and including Canal Street. It is at the latter point where this new construction begins. For an account of same, see, the New York Times
of November 12, 1937.
July 28, 1937.
P. L. Sperr.
